cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object localization and recognition using visual saliency. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on learning a model of visual saliency directly on a robot. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper proposes an autonomous exploration technique using reinforcement learning. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper involves learning and updating a model of visual saliency. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for learning the saliency model.
